I'll look into it, and if necessary change the name.

Dave


On Jan 26, 2004, at 3:53 AM, Marcus Vinicius Eiffle Duarte wrote:

> Hi, folks!
>
> I am a new user of Cantera. Just downloaded it and tried the demos,
> when I found an execution error. It seems that Matlab R13 (6.5) has a
> built-in 'surface' function and so there is a name conflict with the
> Cantare toolbox.
> I wanted to (1) report it, because I don't know if someone else did
> it, and (2) know if there is a newer version of the toolbox with the
> name of this particular function changed (and all the references of
> it in other files).
> I could just change the names myself and send back the toolbox code
> with the changes, but I guess the maintainer(s) of the code would
> like to choose the new name of the function.
> Thank you the great job done in Cantera.
>
> Marcus Vinicius
